                           <locus target="#81va">Fol. 81va</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 81va: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወይዘሮ፡ ምሕረት፡ ግደይ፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀታ፡ ዓመተ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ለመድኃኔ፡ ዓለም፡ ዓዲግራት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወአቡሃ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ወእማኒ፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in the main hand. It mentions the donor, Mǝḥrät Gǝdäy (baptismal name ʿAmätä Maryam), as well as her father Zä-Wäldä Maryam and her mother Wälättä Mädḫǝn. It mentions also the church Mädḫane ʿAläm of ʿAddigrat.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ጳውሎስ is crudely written on the front board with green paint.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names are left unfilled on fols. 7va, 9ra, 19va, 51rb, 56rb, 56va. &#xD;
- Lacunae: fols. 11ra, 32va, 33ra.</item>
                     </list>
